## Description

Removes the `lookup` parameter from `AxiosRequestConfig` as requested in #7271.

Users should now configure custom DNS lookup functions via `httpAgent` or `httpsAgent` options instead, which is the preferred and more idiomatic approach.

## Changes

- Removed `lookup` property from TypeScript type definitions (`index.d.ts`, `index.d.cts`)
- Removed lookup extraction and processing from HTTP adapter (`lib/adapters/http.js`)
- Removed tests that used `config.lookup`

## Breaking Change

⚠️ The `lookup` configuration option has been removed from `AxiosRequestConfig`. 

**Migration:**
```js
// Before (no longer supported)
axios.create({
  lookup: (hostname, opt, cb) => { /* ... */ }
});

// After (use Agent options)
import https from 'https';
axios.create({
  httpsAgent: new https.Agent({
    lookup: (hostname, opt, cb) => { /* ... */ }
  })
});
```

## Testing

- ✅ All 232 unit tests pass
- ✅ TypeScript definitions compile correctly
- ✅ No regressions introduced

Fixes #7271Remove the lookup parameter from AxiosRequestConfig interface as it should only be configured via httpAgent/httpsAgent options.

This addresses issue #7271 by:
- Removing lookup from TypeScript type definitions (index.d.ts, index.d.cts)
- Removing lookup extraction and processing from HTTP adapter
- Updating/removing tests that used config.lookup

BREAKING CHANGE: The lookup configuration option has been removed from AxiosRequestConfig. Users should configure custom DNS lookup via the httpAgent or httpsAgent options instead.

Fixes #7271

